Context: The George Brown College offers computer-related learning options in various areas including computer hardware and networks, computer software and applications, and IT management and digital transformation. Some of the specific skills taught are cloud computing, networking, database administration, computer programming, artificial intelligence, business process automation, and a range of fields within IT management. The college is located on the traditional territory of the Mississaugas of the Credit First Nation and other Indigenous peoples. For more information about the land acknowledgment, visit the college-wide website. Please note that the information contained in this website is subject to change without notice and students are responsible for verifying George Brown College fee requirements.
